            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Josh Lehan",
                        "email": "krellan@google.com",
                        "username": "Krellan"
                    },
                    "message": "This is a good cleanup. I wonder why the static variables were moved outside their functions, though."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Josh Lehan",
                        "email": "krellan@google.com",
                        "username": "Krellan"
                    },
                    "message": "This is a good cleanup, thanks for doing this."
                },
                {
                    "file": "main.cpp",
                    "line": 102,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Josh Lehan",
                        "email": "krellan@google.com",
                        "username": "Krellan"
                    },
                    "message": "I am curious why all these static variables need to move outside their functions. Do these statics need to become globals? In general, it is best to minimize the scope of global variables, to avoid bugs from them being changed accidentally."
                },
                {
                    "file": "main.cpp",
                    "line": 102,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Rudolph",
                        "email": "patrick.rudolph@9elements.com",
                        "username": "PatrickRudolph"
                    },
                    "message": "Those variable need to be modified in stopControlLoops() and restartControlLoops() thus were moved to global scope."
                },
                {
                    "file": "main.cpp",
                    "line": 102,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Josh Lehan",
                        "email": "krellan@google.com",
                        "username": "Krellan"
                    },
                    "message": "Ah. It is still a group of related globals which are all static. Would it be possible to wrap them in a `struct` container? That would make it easier to follow, and cut down on the proliferation of globals. Perhaps name the struct `StartStopState` or something like that."
                },
                {
                    "file": "main.cpp",
                    "line": 102,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Rudolph",
                        "email": "patrick.rudolph@9elements.com",
                        "username": "PatrickRudolph"
                    },
                    "message": "Moving into own namespace."
                }
            ],
